File: A US jury found Johnny Depp and Amber Heard defamed each other. AFP/Valerie Macon FAIRFAX - A US jury has found both Johnny Depp and his ex-wife Amber Heard liable for defamation. The six-week trial revealed the personal lives of both movie stars amid domestic abuse allegations. READ: Key talking points of Depp vs Heard trial The jury awarded the 58-year-old actor $15-million in damages. It found a 2018 article by Heard on her experience of 'sexual violence' defamatory. READ: Jury reaches verdict in Depp vs Heard defamation trial Meanwhile, the 36-year-old actress was awarded $2-million. It followed a statement by Depp's lawyer that Heard's abuse claims were a 'hoax'. READ: Johnny Depp lawyers urge jury to restore his 'name, reputation, career' The Pirates of the Caribbean star, who was not in court, says the jury has given him his life back. Heard says she is heartbroken and disappointed beyond words by the outcome.